title: Spouse or partner of the prime minister of Australia - Wikipedia
snippet: Until the 1960s, it was uncommon for the spouse of a prime minister to have their own career. Zara Holt, a fashion designer, was the first to continue her career during her husband's term in office, and reputedly earned more money than him.

title: Jodie Haydon - Wikipedia
snippet: Jodie Haydon (born 1978 or 1979) is an Australian financial services professional and women's advocate. She is the wife of the 31st (and current) prime minister of Australia, Anthony Albanese.

title: Anthony Albanese - Wikipedia
snippet: Albanese is the first prime minister of Australia to be engaged or wed while in office. Albanese describes himself as "half-Italian and half-Irish" and a "non-practising Catholic". title: Gough Whitlam's partner: Margaret Whitlam | naa.gov.au
snippet: Gough Whitlam was the Prime Minister of Australia from 1972 to 1975. ... From 1972 to 1975, Margaret Whitlam was an outspoken prime ministerial spouse, a frequent guest speaker, broadcaster and columnist.

title: Australian prime minister Albanese becomes first to wed in office
snippet: Anthony Albanese weds Jodie Haydon, after the couple became engaged on Valentine's Day last year.
